The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 19: State-run Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Limited (MTNL) will get a tax refund of Rs 1,380 crore following a direction by the income tax appellate tribunal. The tribunal has directed the I-T department to refund Rs 756 crore to MTNL as tax and Rs 624 crore as interest on it for four assessment years. The windfall tax refund will enable the firm to invest more on its expansion plans.                             
	 New Delhi, March 19: Indias monsoon, crucial for farm output, will be normal this year, union farm secretary Prabeer Kumar Basu said. Going by current weather conditions and El Nino phenomena, the monsoon seem to be normal this year, he said.                            
	 Mumbai, March 19: Bajaj Holdings amp; Investment has hiked its stake in group entity Bajaj Electricals by nearly 19 per cent for Rs 77 crore, taking its total stake to 31.65 per cent. Bajaj Holdings has bought 36.69 lakh shares, or 18.80 per cent in the firm, for Rs 76.88 crore through open-market transactions.                            
	 Mumbai, March 19: The Securities Appellate Tribunal has dismissed the review application filed by First Globals Shankar Sharma against its earlier order upholding a Sebi ruling, which barred him from accessing the securities market.                            
	 New Delhi, March 19: State-run Bank of Baroda (BoB), Andhra Bank and UK-based Legal amp; General have launched IndiaFirst Life Insurance company. The venture is capitalised at Rs 330 crore, with BoB holding a 44 per cent stake followed by Andhra Bank at 30 per cent.                                                                                                                          
